================================================================================
AURUM PROTOCOL - AGENT PIPELINE DOCUMENTATION
================================================================================

OVERVIEW
--------
Aurum is an autonomous AI credit bureau built on Casper Network. The system
uses six specialized AI agents orchestrated by LangGraph to generate verifiable
on-chain credit profiles for wallets, AI agents, DAOs, and businesses.

All agents use Groq-powered Llama 3.3 70B for LLM reasoning with fallback to
rule-based logic if LLM calls fail.


================================================================================
AGENT 1: CREDIT AGENT
================================================================================

PURPOSE
-------
Generates credit scores (0-1000) using XGBoost machine learning model with
SHAP explainability. This is the only deterministic (non-LLM) agent by design
to ensure consistent and auditable credit scoring.

WHAT IT DOES
------------
- Takes wallet address as input
- Scores wallet across six dimensions (0-100 each):
  * Repayment history
  * Wallet activity
  * DeFi engagement
  * DAO participation
  * RWA ownership
  * Income consistency
- Runs XGBoost trained on synthetic wallet profiles
- Generates SHAP feature importance breakdown
- Outputs final credit score 0-1000

WORKFLOW
--------
1. Receive wallet_address from pipeline state
2. Generate mock wallet data (transaction counts, volume, diversity)
3. Create 6-dimensional feature vector
4. Run XGBoost predict() to get credit score
5. Run SHAP explain() to get feature contributions
6. Return credit_score, sub_scores, shap_breakdown

OUTPUTS
-------
- credit_score: int (0-1000)
- sub_scores: dict with 6 dimension scores
- shap_breakdown: dict with feature importance values
- raw_wallet_data: dict with wallet metrics

