================================================================================
PIPELINE ORCHESTRATION
================================================================================

EXECUTION FLOW
--------------
Credit Agent --> Risk Agent --> Fraud Agent --> Attestation Agent -->
Monitoring Agent --> Lending Agent --> END

LANGGRAPH STRUCTURE
-------------------
- Uses StateGraph with PipelineState TypedDict
- Linear execution (no conditional branching)
- Each agent receives full state and returns updated state
- All outputs accumulated in single state object

API KEY DISTRIBUTION
--------------------
GROQ_API_KEY (Key 1):
- Fraud Agent
- Risk Agent
- Monitoring Agent

GROQ_API_KEY_1 (Key 2):
- Attestation Agent
- Lending Agent

This distribution prevents single API key rate limit exhaustion.


================================================================================
SHARED UTILITIES
================================================================================

LOCATION
--------
agents/utils/llm_utils.py

AGENTLLM CLASS
--------------
Manages shared LLM instances to eliminate redundancy:
- get_llm(key_name): Returns cached Groq ChatGroq instance
- parse_json_response(response): Handles markdown code blocks
- invoke_llm(llm, prompt): Calls LLM and parses JSON

PROMPTS CLASS
-------------
Centralized prompt templates for all agents:
- fraud_detection()
- risk_analysis()
- attestation_summary()
- credential_monitoring()
- lending_recommendation()

All prompts request JSON responses and include detailed context.


